'''Darren Craddock''' (born [[February 23]] [[1985]]) is a [[footballer (soccer)|footballer]] who currently plays for [[York City F.C.|York City]].

==Football career==

===Hartlepool United===

Craddock was handed his first professional contract by Hartlepool United in 2004.<ref name="Craddock earns Pools deal">{{cite news
| title = Craddock earns Pools deal
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/h/hartlepool_united/3826665.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = [[2004-06-21]]
| accessdate = 2007-03-05}}</ref> Craddock was signed by York City on a months loan in January 2006.<ref name="Craddock makes York loan switch">{{cite news
| title = Craddock makes York loan switch
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/y/york_city/4630952.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = [[2006-01-20]]
| accessdate = 2007-03-05}}</ref> Craddock was released by Hartlepool United at the end of the 2005/06 season.<ref name="Seven players released by Pools">{{cite news
| title = Seven players released by Pools
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/h/hartlepool_united/4758721.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = [[2006-05-10]]
| accessdate = 2007-03-05}}</ref>

===York City===

Craddock was signed by York City following his release by Hartlepool United in May 2006.<ref name="McEwan recruits ex-Pools defender">{{cite news
| title = McEwan recruits ex-Pools defender
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/y/york_city/5034222.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = [[2006-05-31]]
| accessdate = 2007-03-05}}</ref>

Craddock was warned he could face a spell on the sidelines by manager [[Billy McEwan]] after receiving a one-match ban after he was booked for fouling [[Forest Green Rovers F.C.|Forest Green Rovers]] striker Allan Russell after losing possession on the halfway line.<ref name="Banned Craddock comes under fire from McEwan">{{cite news
| title = Banned Craddock comes under fire from McEwan
| url = http://www.yorkpress.co.uk/sport/yorkcityfc/news/display.var.1055298.0.banned_craddock_comes_under_fire_from_mcewan.php
| publisher = The Press
| date = [[2006-12-04]]
| accessdate = 2007-01-18}}</ref>

Craddock will miss the rest of the 2006/07 season due to a fractured jaw, which was sustained against [[Cambridge United F.C.|Cambridge United]].<ref name="Darren Craddock Injury Woe">{{cite news
| title = Darren Craddock Injury Woe
| url = http://www.ycfc.net/news/march07/13.php
| publisher = York City FC
| date = [[2007-03-15]]
| accessdate = 2007-03-15}}</ref>

